result.execSummary:
The defendant was charged with both OWI (3rd) and Operating w/ PAC (3rd). The defendant was found guilty of OWI (3rd) and the other charge, Operating w/ PAC (3rd) was dismissed by the court.

  • Ashley M. Martorana was found guilty of OWI (3rd), an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 346.63(1)(a).
  • Ashley M. Martorana was found guilty of Possession of THC, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(e).
  • Ashley M. Martorana was found guilty of Possession of Narcotic Drugs, a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(am).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Case Called @ 9:15 AM: Defendant Ashley M. Martorana in court with attorney Ryan Scott Ulrich.  Steven Paul Anderson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Joint recommendation as to Ct Nos 3 and 4.  State will cap and argue as to Ct 1 offense.  State moves to amend Ct No 1 to OWI 3 based upon conviction recently in Marquette Co.  Ct 3 Amended to Misd Level THC.  ADA states there was no request for Blood Draw Cost received.  Def and counsel concur w/State's recital.  Court entertains waiver of pre-lim hearing as to Ct 3, 4 and 5.  Court accepts knowing and voluntary waiver of pre-lim hearing in its entirety.  Def BOT.  INFO Filed.  Receipt Admitted - Reading Waived.  Def and counsel confirm pleas to be entered today.  Defendant advised of minimum/maximum penalty.  Terms of bifurcated SEH explained.  Agrees w/2 prior convictions as to Ct 1 offense.  Def confirms recent conviction for OWI 2 in Marquette Co.  Court receives into the record in this case the CCAP record of conviction and Judicial Dash that establishes that conviction for OWI 2.  Counsel confirm same.   Plea QN reviewed w/Defendant.  Plea colloquy entertained.  Collateral consequences explained.  Chapter 950 compliance addressed.  Plea Ct 1 - As Amended to 3rd Offense OWI:  NC   Amended upon motion of the State - Plea Ct 3 - Amended to Misd Level THC:  NC Plea Ct 4 as charged:  NC   5/6/2014 is Date of offense in Marquette CoO - receives CCAP information provided.  Court accepts knowing and voluntary pleas and enters JOC.  Ct 2 dismissed outright.  Ct Nos 5 and 6 and 2014TR000905 all DRI.  Argument by ADA as to penalty on Ct 1.  Argument by Atty Ulrich as to penalty on Ct 1 - agrees with recommendation as to Ct Nos 3 and 4.  Atty Ulrich argues for lesser jail time due to sanction sentence being served - 54 days consecutive to sanction SEH.  54 days plus 21 days on sanction sentence would also equal 75.  Believes 6 days of TS credit exists.  State is in agreement with TS credit of 6 days.  Statement by Def:  Yes.  Def has 8 days left to serve on sanction sentence.  The Court:  OWI 3 Sentence Imposed - 60 days WCJ, concurrent to any existing SEH - net result is additional 37 days actual time to serve on Ct 1 sentence which is 50 days jail with GT credit applied, Huber, 6 days TS credit; $2017 Fine inclusive with DNA Surcharge - bond posted to be applied with , No Blood Draw Fee,  28 mos DL Rev/IID for 28 mos commencing today; OWI assessment prior to relicensing; Ct Nos. 3 and 4:  S/W - 2 yrs probation.  Concurrent to any existing supervision Def is currently under.  Conditions:  AODA and any follow thru as deemed appropriate; the defendant must maintain absolute sobriety, may not be present upon the premises of any bars, and is prohibited from possessing/ingesting any impairing substances that have not been prescribed by a physician; maintain gainful employment; Court Costs with DNA surcharge.  Def to make Marquette Co Agent aware of today's conviction.  Appeal Rights Given.
